{%- comment -%}
  ============================================================================
  BFC WARRANTY TIERS — JS lookup table — snippets/bfc-warranty-tiers-js.liquid

  Drops a JS array (BFC_WARRANTY_TIERS) into the page that lets variant-change
  handlers re-pick the correct warranty variant when the customer switches
  camera variant on the PDP.

  Usage (inside a <script> block in the PDP):
    {% render 'bfc-warranty-tiers-js', category: 'slr' %}

  Outputs an array of {max, ...} objects, indexed by tier (0..10):
    max  = upper bound in cents for that price tier

  For SLR / Polaroid / MF (single +6 mo button):
    v12, p12 — the +6 month variant

  For PAS (3 buttons +3/+6/+9):
    v6, p6   — the +3 month variant (6 mo total)
    v9, p9   — the +6 month variant (9 mo total)
    v12, p12 — the +9 month variant (12 mo total)
    Note: PAS v6 and v9 max out at tier 6 ($1001-$1500). Tiers 7-10 reuse the
    tier 6 variant for those buttons; v12 has unique variants for all 11 tiers.

  Updated 2026-05-13 with the new bfc-extended-warranty-new product variants.
  ============================================================================
{%- endcomment -%}

